Rating: 4
This is a winning recipe. You know it's good when your family continues to compliment you throughout the night even when dinner is long over. The only change I made was I substituted creme fraiche for the whipping cream and added a little cornstarch to the broth. The sauce was as smooth as velvet, not runny, and the taste was delicious. These two changes, I believe, made all the difference.

Rating: 4
This is a favorite in our house. I made a few minor changes. I cubed the beef and browned it in olive oil with lots of ground pepper. I then followed the recipe but used non fat sour cream instead of cream. I put the browned beef into the sauce and mushroom mix and let it thicken (option - thicken by mixing broth with corn starch in a cup and then stir into the pan) then serve in a bowl over the noodles. Great, fast and simple!

Rating: 4
