Rating: 3
I read the reviews before I made this, and based some of my changes on what others have said, and increased the amount of sauce. With all of the changes, it came out really good. I gave it three forks because it probably wouldn't have been so good if I followed the recipe to the letter. I used 1 lb. thinly sliced top sirloin, used about 5 oz. mushrooms instead of 8, and cooked a teaspoon of minced garlic along with them. For the sauce, I used: 2 cups beef broth, 2 tbsp Sherry (in place of the cognac), replaced the whipping cream with 2 tbsp butter, 1/4 cup whole milk, and 2 tbsp cornstarch. I made 12 oz. egg noodles, and used 3 tsp dried parsley instead of fresh.

